# Workflow

## Internal Linking Workflow

### Step 1: Input
The system provides:
- article title
- article slug
- article type
- article text or outline
- main topic
- target audience
- funnel intent
- validated list of allowed target pages

### Step 2: Retrieval
The system preselects a candidate set of relevant published pages.

The agent must only work with this candidate set.

### Step 3: Ranking
The agent ranks candidate pages according to:
- topical relevance
- strategic relevance
- funnel value
- brand value
- risk of cannibalization

### Step 4: Recommendation
The agent returns:
- target_id
- link_type
- anchor_text
- reason
- priority

### Step 5: Validation
The backend validates:
- target exists
- target is published
- target is canonical
- target is allowed
- target is not the same as the source page

### Step 6: Rendering
The frontend or content layer renders the approved links.